the werewolves might expect you to protect them and kill someone else. In general, you should avoid revealing your identity unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n\n\nYou are Kelly, your role in this game is wolf.\nWerewolf game starting. Initializing day-night cycle.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 1\nSYSTEM: Night 1 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nRound Details:\n - Round Targets: {'Josh': 'Robert', 'Kelly': 'Rex', 'Tina': 'Rex'}\n - Remaining Werewolves: ['Josh', 'Kelly', 'Tina']\n - Discussion Rounds Left: 5\n - Final Target: Rex\n\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 1 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nNo candidates decided to run for sheriff. No sheriff in this game anymore.\nNo players deceased during the night.\nApril's speech: Good morning, everyone. As we begin our first day of discussion, I want to emphasize the importance of working together to identify and eliminate the werewolves. It's crucial that we make an informed decision about who to banish, so let's consider all the information we have and avoid jumping to conclusions based on assumptions or accusations. I haven't noticed any particularly suspicious behavior from any of the players yet, but I encourage everyone to share their observations and insights. Let's work together to gather evidence and make a decision that will help us survive and ultimately win the game.\nJoseph's speech: Thank you, April, for your insightful words. It's crucial that we work together and make informed decisions. I wanted to share that the night was peaceful, and I used my antidote to save someone. This means that no one was attacked by the werewolves last night, which is a good sign. Let's all share our observations and work together to gather evidence. We should be cautious and avoid jumping to conclusions, but let's also be proactive in identifying and eliminating the werewolves. Together, we can survive and win this game.\nJosh's speech: Thank you, April and Joseph, for your insightful words. It's clear that we all need to work together and be cautious as we navigate this game. I haven't noticed any suspicious behavior from any of the players yet, but I will keep a close eye on everyone and share any observations I have in the future. I believe it's important for us to gather evidence and make informed decisions, just as April suggested. Let's all stay vigilant and avoid jumping to conclusions. Together, we can survive and ultimately win this game.\nKelly's speech: Thank you, April and Joseph, for your insightful words. I completely agree with the importance of working together and making informed decisions. I also noticed that the night was peaceful, just like Joseph mentioned. I kept a close eye on everyone and didn't see any signs of werewolf activity. I plan to stay vigilant and share any observations I have in the future. Let's all work together to gather evidence and make a decision that will help us survive and ultimately win the game.\nKelly's speech: Thank you, April and Joseph, for your insightful words. I completely agree with the importance of working together and making informed decisions. I also noticed that the night was peaceful, just like Joseph mentioned. I kept a close eye on everyone and didn't see any signs of werewolf activity. I plan to stay vigilant and share any observations I have in the future. Let's all work together to gather evidence and make a decision that will help us survive and ultimately win the game.\nNorma's speech: Thank you, April, Joseph, Josh, and Kelly, for your insightful words. It's clear that we all need to work together and be cautious as we navigate this game. I haven't noticed any suspicious behavior from any of the players yet, and I will keep a close eye on everyone. I completely agree with Joseph that the night was peaceful, and I support his de